content: Presidential election in Singapore Indirect presidential elections were held in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) on 30 August 1985, following the resignation of the incumbent, [Devan Nair](/wiki/Devan_Nair). During the election, 73 members of Parliament were present and five members were absent. [Wee Kim Wee](/wiki/Wee_Kim_Wee) was elected by the [Parliament of Singapore](/wiki/Parliament_of_Singapore).
